caption: I highly recommend this deli.  The food is excellent and always well-prepared and timely.  They use Boars Head, which is a must for delis.  It's surprising how few delis in DC have BH.  The salads are great too.  The people who run the deli are very warm and friendly.  I've lived in NYC and the tri-state area and grew up on good delis, and I can confidently say this is a good deli.

Quick review: Very impressed. Quick dine in or out, easy spot to wait to be picked up by car, and delicious food. Large menu, not so well for off-the-street people but good to keep you coming back. Employees know their stuff and are always working to keep the store clean and help customers. Prices a bit much, but expected for DC. Plenty of decent indoor and outdoor seating.  Long review: Accessibility is nice, just across the street from the Marriot Marquis. You can also wait inside or outside while waiting for people to pick you up in a car.  Menu is large, hard to get a good grasp on what they have available if you're just walking in off the street. But if you like going to the same place over and over, the variety will definitely keep you coming back.  Food is delicious and doesn't take too long to make. I ordered the New Yorker sandwich, and a Twilight Delight smoothie and both took about ten minutes.  Staff is smiling, friendly, and quick. They're always moving and working to clean the store and help customers.  Prices are a little high, paying nearly $16 just for a sandwich and smoothie is a bit much, but also expected in DC.  Seating is nice and spaced, chairs off in the corner and comfortable cushioned stools. Outside tables are great for sunny weather.
Fast & Casual & Quality

West Wing Cafe has good reviews on Yelp. Here's my experience:  1) Space: It's close to the Convention Center and large. There's plenty of seats indoor and a few outdoor too.  2) Food: They sells snacks, sandwiches, coffee, etc. I ordered the ham, cheese, and egg breakfast bagel. It was decent and very filling. The coffee is brewed from La Colombe.  3) Service: They are nice, but it took them around 20 minutes to make my bagel and it wasn't insanely busy.
